</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-dPiLbb jGEmDy pf-26_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXeWAj cnchaw pf-27_"><div class="sc-dPiLbb jGEmDy pf-28_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXeWAj cnchaw pf-29_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ehCJOs bPBLAf pf-30_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iWVNaa eCsXSR pf-32_">What is customer service?</span></h2><p class="sc-dwsnSq jqylDz pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iWVNaa eCsXSR pf-35_">Customer service refers to the help and guidance a business offers consumers who purchase or utilise its goods or services. Every industry has specific standards for customer service, but ultimately, the goal of a well-performed service is to boost profits. Employees who can modify themselves to the customer's personality are critical to the perceived effectiveness of customer service encounters.
<br><br>Customer service practices frequently show a company's strategies and ideals. Customer retention is typically used to gauge how well customer service is performing. For some businesses, providing excellent customer service is one of their intangible assets that sets them apart from competitors. One positive customer service encounter might alter how a consumer views the company.
</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="pf-c pf-sm-hide pf-hide" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXeWAj cnchaw pf-36_ pf-sm-hide pf-hide"></div></div></div><div class="sc-dPiLbb jGEmDy pf-37_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXeWAj cnchaw pf-38_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXeWAj cnchaw pf-39_"><div class="sc-dPiLbb jGEmDy pf-40_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXeWAj cnchaw pf-41_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ehCJOs bPBLAf pf-42_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iWVNaa eCsXSR pf-44_">What is social media customer service?</span></h2><p class="sc-dwsnSq jqylDz pf-45_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iWVNaa eCsXSR pf-47_">The process of using social media to address customer complaints is known as social media customer service. Because clients can contact your staff on the platforms they currently use, social customer care is quite effective. Implementing social media customer care is worthwhile since it significantly improves client experiences and your brand. Giving customers a choice to contact you readily via social media can ultimately enhance customer satisfaction.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-dPiLbb jGEmDy pf-48_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXeWAj cnchaw pf-49_"><div class="sc-dPiLbb jGEmDy pf-50_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXeWAj cnchaw pf-51_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ehCJOs bPBLAf pf-52_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iWVNaa eCsXSR pf-54_">Why is social media customer service important?</span></h2><p class="sc-dwsnSq jqylDz pf-55_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iWVNaa eCsXSR pf-57_">Here are some justifications for why customer service on social media is essential:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-iqVWFU kwUChp pf-58_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-eWfVMQ HLdwB pf-59_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iWVNaa eCsXSR pf-61_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">More vital brand awareness</span> - Activating a company account on social media is necessary to increase online awareness by constantly appearing on a prospect's newsfeed.
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-eWfVMQ HLdwB pf-62_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iWVNaa eCsXSR pf-64_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Connects you to your customers</span> - You're enabling your customers to learn more about your company if you regularly offer helpful material on a channel where they hang out. 
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-eWfVMQ HLdwB pf-65_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iWVNaa eCsXSR pf-67_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Engages your customers</span> - Engagement is vital when developing a brand or community for your customers. Furthermore, there are countless options; you can run contests, distribute original material, give immediate assistance, and more. 
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-eWfVMQ HLdwB pf-68_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iWVNaa eCsXSR pf-70_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Increases personalisation</span> -The engagement rises as each encounter gets increasingly tailored to the individual. You can do this without being obtrusive via social media.
</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-eWfVMQ HLdwB pf-71_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-iWVNaa eCsXSR pf-73_"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Quick response times</span> - The more immediately you respond to the customers and even express your sincerest apologies, the more your customers will be pleasantly surprised and satisfied.
